  4 0x00000322 0x00000322 1267 1267         ascii s scorecard.       \r\n*Water\r\nTrolling for Nessie is more fun than searching for shots that end up here.  More evidence that golf balls do not float.    \r\n*Maple Tree\r\nGetting past this obstacle and back onto the fairway without bodily injury is an honorable goal (press <tab> to size).\r\n*Pine\r\nHitting a solid shot out of the mess of needles and cones this tree deposits on the course is a chance event (press <tab> to size).\r\n*Scots Pine\r\nA sticky-armed creature that gathers errant shots and blocks any attempts to salvage par (press <tab> to size).  \r\n*Fairway\r\nNeatly clipped colonial bent grasses promote healthy bounces and lengthy rolls.  A natural place to rest on the way to the green.\r\n*Firm Fairway\r\nShort, tight grass on compacted soil.  Shots landing here travel with more urgency toward green and bunker alike.\r\n*Deep rough\r\nWild, tangled grasses inflate scores and humble club members.  Tough to get out without a sickle.\r\n*Waste bunker\r\nA traditional bunker dotted with patches of gorse and brush.  As if a traditional sand bunker isn't hard enough...  \r\n*Gorse\r\nLittle yellow blooms belie its evil intent; takes balls and keeps 'em.\r\n*Rocks\r\nNatural formations produce unnatural bounces.  Leaves scars on balls, clubs, and players' psyches.\r\n\r\n*END\r\n
